title: Spartan stunner: MSU 27, U-M 23
text: Facebook Email Twitter Google+ LinkedIn Pinterest Spartan stunner: MSU 27, U-M 23 The craziest finish in the history of the in-state rivalry saw the Spartans score a game-winning TD on U-M botched punt Post to Facebook Spartan stunner: MSU 27, U-M 23 The craziest finish in the history of the in-state rivalry saw the Spartans score a game-winning TD on U-M botched punt Check out this story on lansingstatejournal.com: http://on.lsj.com/1ROQV6T Cancel Send A link has been sent to your friend's email address. A link has been posted to your Facebook feed. 9 To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Spartan stunner: MSU 27, U-M 23 Joe Rexrode, Detroit Free Press 11:51 p.m. EDT October 17, 2015 Buy Photo Jalen Watts-Jackson (20) crosses the goal line to score the winning touchdown after time expired to claim the win and the Paul Bunyan trophy for Michigan State in a 27-23 over Michigan Saturday, October 17, 2015, at Michigan Stadium in Ann Arbor. Watts-Jackson recovered a muffed punt for a touchdown. Dave Wasinger/Lansing State Journal Fullscreen Buy Photo Michigan State tight end Josiah Price screams as he celebrates with teammates after a thrilling, last-second 27-23 victory over Michigan Saturday, October 17, 2015, in Ann Arbor. Dave Wasinger/Lansing State Journal MSU's Arjen Colquhoun, left, and Connor Cook, right, carry the winning Paul Bunyan trophy in Michigan Stadium after teammate Jalen Watts-Jackson ran back a Michigan fumbled or muffed punt for a touchdown and a 27-23 win Saturday 10/17/2015. Rod Sanford | Lansing State JJournal Fullscreen Buy Photo Michigan State players celebrate in the endzone after a last-second 27-23 victory over Michigan Saturday, October 17, 2015 in Ann Arbor. Dave Wasinger/Lansing State Journal Fullscreen Buy Photo Michigan State quarterback Connor Cook smiles as he hugs Quarterbacks Coach Brad Salem after the Spartans 27-23 victory over Michigan Saturday, October 17, 2015, in Michigan Stadium. Dave Wasinger/Lansing State Journal Fullscreen Buy Photo Spartans Khari Willis (27), Monty Madaris (88) and others celebrate in the endzone as Michigan players look on after Jalen Watts-Jackson scored the winning touchdown after time expired to beat the Wolverines 27-23 Saturday, October 17, 2015, at Michigan Stadium in Ann Arbor. Dave Wasinger/Lansing State Journal Fullscreen Buy Photo Jalen Watts-Jackson (20) is lifted onto a stretcher before being carted off the field after Michigan State's 27-23 win over Michigan Saturday, October 17, 2015, at Michigan Stadium in Ann Arbor. Watts-Jackson recovered a fumble for a touchdown after time expired. He was hurt in the ensuing celebration. Preliminary reports are that he broke or dislocated his hip.
